WRITING.TEXT: Oct 1 2020 7:01pm I just had the weirdest and for some reason the saddest dream in my life to the point where even when i woke up i felt like shit. Anyways the dream went like this... I was up on a stage about to perform a concert with two other people one was playing the piano and one the guitar. I felt out of place and uncomfortable + I didn't have an instrument I could play so I was panicking. I walked over to this big white soundboard and i was like AHHHHHH i've never played a soundboard in my life so I started panicking again but then the guy who was playing the guitar to my left walked over to me and reached behind a pile of equipment and pulled out a smaller soundboard with the buttons shaped like piano keys, #8220;the instrument i could play #8221; and said #8220;just have fun #8221;. I grabbed the new sound board and tried to accompany the other two. It was going smoothly and then when we were coming to the end the song started to go slow so I played more restrained and quiet then the girl who was playing piano to my right and complemented my dynamics. The song came to an end then the guy said to come over to my house so me and the girl were like ok. Once we got to the house for some reason we were just chilling in the middle of a long hallway when the guy brought out two joysticks and so we started playing games. The first round was the other two fighting each other in a weird all to realistic mecha fighting game that felt like we were inside of it. The girl won so then she challenged me so i started playing and it felt like i was inside of the game, she teached me the controls then killed me the first round and i proceeded to button mash her to death in the second round. After the second round we were back in the house and she was walking out of the hallway and into the kitchen which looked very similar to the kitchen in my house in real life. She then grabbed a chair and sat in the corner and was talking to me and asked can if she could pay a song for me so i nodded and she grabbed a ukulele from seemingly nowhere #8220;dream logic #8221; then began to play a song and idk why but it felt really nostalgic and i was humming along then the dream ended. For some reason even though the dream sounds fun it felt like it had an air of loneliness so when I woke up I felt/still feel absolutely horrible. On the bright side this is the first dream I #8217;ve had in months where I didn #8217;t die a gruesome death. Even then why do all of my dreams have to feel so real and made me feel so bad when I wake up.
